# MUTANT: jr-off-by-one  (domain: emulator-gb)
# ============================================================================
# DEFECT (one): the relative jump JR computes the target PC off by one — it adds
# the signed displacement WITHOUT first advancing PC past the 2-byte JR opcode
# (or double-counts). INVARIANTS/golden: JR e at 0x0103 with e=+2 -> target =
# 0x0103 + 2 (instr length) + 2 (e) = 0x0107. The mutant lands at 0x0106 (forgot
# to add the +2 instruction length, or counted from the opcode byte). PC is the
# silent killer: a 1-byte JR target error desynchronizes the entire downstream
# trace.
#
# must_turn_red_gate: emulator-gb trace-diff (PC field + downstream desync)
# how_the_gate_rejects: the trace-diff compares PC line-for-line. After the JR,
#   reference PC=0x0107, mutant PC=0x0106 -> divergence at that line, and the
#   PCMEM bytes differ too (0x00,... at 0107 vs whatever sits at 0106). The diff
#   pins it to the exact instruction. Flags are correct (JR sets none) so a
#   flag-only check would MISS it — only the PC/trace diff catches the off-by-one.
#
# Same program as golden. The ONLY corrupted line is the post-JR state (L5):
#   reference: A:01 F:20 ... PC:0107 PCMEM:00,00,00,00   (correct +2+2 target)
#   mutant:    A:01 F:20 ... PC:0106 PCMEM:02,00,00,00   (off by one)  <-- DEFECT
# (0x0106 is the byte AFTER the JR operand; PCMEM there starts with the 0x02 e-byte's
#  neighbor / stray byte, NOT the 0x00 NOP at 0x0107 — the desync is visible in PCMEM too.)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
A:01 F:B0 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0100 PCMEM:3C,3D,A7,18
A:02 F:10 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0101 PCMEM:3D,A7,18,02
A:01 F:50 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0102 PCMEM:A7,18,02,00
A:01 F:20 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0103 PCMEM:18,02,00,00
A:01 F:20 B:00 C:13 D:00 E:D8 H:01 L:4D SP:FFFE PC:0106 PCMEM:02,00,00,00
# diverging_line_index: 4 (0-based) — PC: reference 0x0107 vs mutant 0x0106 (+ PCMEM desync)
# invariant_violated: JR target = PC_after_operand + signed_e. blind_to: all flags (JR sets none), all registers.
